Multi-hop routing test with 4 nodes in a line topology.

Tests:
1) Route propagation across multiple hops
2) Multi-hop DATA packet forwarding in both directions
3) Convergence time for 3-hop network
4) Route cost accumulation (10 + 20 + 15 = 45ms)

Expected behavior:
- Node 1 learns route to node 4 via node 2, then via node 3
- Node 4 learns route to node 1 via node 3, then via node 2
- DATA packets traverse all intermediate nodes
- Routing tables fully converge by ~60s (2 DV update rounds)
